[ LEVEL - BASIC (FIRST INHERITANCE) ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  01. CREATE A PARENT CLASS.
  02. CREATE A CHILD CLASS INHERITING PARENT.
  03. CREATE OBJECT OF CHILD CLASS.
  04. ACCESS PARENT ATTRIBUTES FROM CHILD.
  05. ACCESS PARENT METHODS FROM CHILD.
  06. OVERRIDE PARENT METHOD IN CHILD.
  07. CALL PARENT METHOD FROM CHILD.
  08. ADD NEW METHOD IN CHILD.
  09. ADD NEW ATTRIBUTE IN CHILD.
  10. SHOW PARENT AND CHILD ATTRIBUTES SEPARATELY.
  11. CHECK ISINSTANCE() FOR CHILD OBJECT.
  12. CHECK ISSUBCLASS() FOR CHILD CLASS.
  13. CREATE PARENT WITH CONSTRUCTOR.
  14. CALL PARENT CONSTRUCTOR FROM CHILD.
  15. OVERRIDE CONSTRUCTOR IN CHILD.
  16. USE SUPER() TO CALL PARENT CONSTRUCTOR.
  17. FORGET SUPER() AND OBSERVE BEHAVIOR.
  18. FIX MISSING PARENT INITIALIZATION.
  19. PRINT MRO (METHOD RESOLUTION ORDER).
  20. COMPARE PARENT VS CHILD BEHAVIOR.

[ LEVEL 1 ‚Äî VERY BASIC (MULTI-LEVEL INHERITANCE) ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  21. CREATE GRANDPARENT ‚Üí PARENT ‚Üí CHILD CLASSES.
  22. ACCESS GRANDPARENT METHOD FROM CHILD.
  23. OVERRIDE METHOD AT PARENT LEVEL.
  24. OVERRIDE SAME METHOD AT CHILD LEVEL.
  25. CALL OVERRIDDEN METHOD USING SUPER().
  26. OBSERVE METHOD RESOLUTION ORDER.
  27. PRINT ATTRIBUTES FROM ALL LEVELS.
  28. TRACK CONSTRUCTOR CALL ORDER.
  29. ADD ATTRIBUTE AT EACH LEVEL.
  30. MODIFY ATTRIBUTE AT CHILD LEVEL.
  31. PREVENT ATTRIBUTE OVERRIDE.
  32. SHADOW PARENT ATTRIBUTE.
  33. RESTORE PARENT BEHAVIOR.
  34. USE PARENT LOGIC PARTIALLY.
  35. COMBINE PARENT + CHILD LOGIC.
  36. DEBUG INHERITANCE CHAIN.
  37. CREATE REAL-WORLD HIERARCHY (PERSON ‚Üí STUDENT).
  38. CREATE REAL-WORLD HIERARCHY (EMPLOYEE ‚Üí MANAGER).
  39. CREATE REAL-WORLD HIERARCHY (VEHICLE ‚Üí CAR ‚Üí EV).
  40. VALIDATE INHERITANCE DESIGN.

[ LEVEL 2 ‚Äî BASIC (MULTIPLE INHERITANCE) ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  41. CREATE TWO PARENT CLASSES.
  42. CREATE CHILD INHERITING FROM BOTH PARENTS.
  43. ACCESS METHODS FROM BOTH PARENTS.
  44. OVERRIDE COMMON METHOD.
  45. OBSERVE MRO IN MULTIPLE INHERITANCE.
  46. PRINT MRO EXPLICITLY.
  47. RESOLVE METHOD CONFLICT MANUALLY.
  48. USE SUPER() IN MULTIPLE INHERITANCE.
  49. FORGET COOPERATIVE SUPER() AND DEBUG.
  50. FIX DIAMOND PROBLEM.
  51. CREATE DIAMOND INHERITANCE STRUCTURE.
  52. DEMONSTRATE AMBIGUITY PROBLEM.
  53. RESOLVE AMBIGUITY USING MRO.
  54. COMBINE BEHAVIORS FROM BOTH PARENTS.
  55. MIX UTILITY + BUSINESS CLASS.
  56. MIX LOGGING + SERVICE CLASS.
  57. MIX VALIDATION + DATA CLASS.
  58. USE MIXIN CLASS PATTERN.
  59. CREATE REUSABLE MIXIN.
  60. DESIGN SAFE MULTIPLE INHERITANCE.

[ LEVEL 3 ‚Äî BASIC+ (POLYMORPHISM) ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  61. SAME METHOD NAME, DIFFERENT BEHAVIOR.
  62. CALL SAME METHOD ON DIFFERENT OBJECTS.
  63. DEMONSTRATE RUNTIME POLYMORPHISM.
  64. USE PARENT REFERENCE FOR CHILD OBJECT.
  65. STORE DIFFERENT CHILD OBJECTS IN LIST.
  66. CALL SAME METHOD IN LOOP.
  67. OVERRIDE BEHAVIOR DYNAMICALLY.
  68. REPLACE OBJECT WITH ANOTHER SUBCLASS.
  69. BUILD FUNCTION ACCEPTING PARENT TYPE.
  70. CALL OVERRIDDEN METHOD INTERNALLY.
  71. DEMONSTRATE POLYMORPHIC BEHAVIOR CLEARLY.
  72. COMPARE PROCEDURAL VS POLYMORPHIC SOLUTION.
  73. REMOVE CONDITIONALS USING POLYMORPHISM.
  74. REFACTOR IF-ELSE LOGIC INTO CLASSES.
  75. DEMONSTRATE OPEN-CLOSED PRINCIPLE.
  76. ADD NEW SUBCLASS WITHOUT MODIFYING CODE.
  77. DEMONSTRATE LATE BINDING.
  78. DEBUG POLYMORPHISM ERRORS.
  79. BUILD POLYMORPHIC CALCULATOR.
  80. BUILD POLYMORPHIC PAYMENT SYSTEM.

[ LEVEL 4 ‚Äî MEDIUM (ABSTRACTION) ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  81. CREATE ABSTRACT BASE CLASS.
  82. CREATE ABSTRACT METHOD.
  83. CREATE CONCRETE SUBCLASS.
  84. IMPLEMENT ABSTRACT METHOD.
  85. TRY INSTANTIATING ABSTRACT CLASS (FAIL).
  86. FIX BY IMPLEMENTING METHODS.
  87. ADD MULTIPLE ABSTRACT METHODS.
  88. ENFORCE IMPLEMENTATION IN SUBCLASS.
  89. USE ABSTRACT CLASS REFERENCE.
  90. OVERRIDE ABSTRACT METHODS.
  91. COMBINE ABSTRACTION + INHERITANCE.
  92. COMBINE ABSTRACTION + POLYMORPHISM.
  93. DESIGN INTERFACE-LIKE STRUCTURE.
  94. BUILD PLUGIN INTERFACE.
  95. BUILD SERVICE INTERFACE.
  96. BUILD REPOSITORY INTERFACE.
  97. BUILD NOTIFIER INTERFACE.
  98. BUILD PAYMENT GATEWAY INTERFACE.
  99. BUILD STORAGE INTERFACE.
 100. VALIDATE ABSTRACTION DESIGN.

